Associated Terms for Data Foundation

Activation: The process that publishes a segment to activation platforms (targets).
Activation Target: The location, including authentication and authorization information, where a segmentâ€™s data is being sent to during activation.
Attributes: Information or data found in objects.
Direct attributes (1:1): Attributes that have a direct relationship in a data model object.
Related attributes (1:N): Attributes that have a one-to-many (1:N) relationship.

Individual: An Individual profile represents an instance of a person from an external system, such as a SubscriberKey.
Segment: A grouping of data that shares some set of characteristics.
Unified Individual: A Unified Individual is a grouping of separate Individual profiles that relate to a single Unified Individual profile.

Marketing Cloud Engagement Terms

Attribute: Information or data about a contact found in a data extension created as part of a Data Cloud activation.
Attribute Group: A logical grouping of data extensions that make up the Contact Model within Engagement.
Contact Model: A collection of attribute groups that define a person within Engagement.
Data Extension: A table that stores data in Engagement.

Data Foundation Terms

Core Audience Model: Two core data extensions are connected to the Engagement Contact Model for content personalization and decisioning across many different Journey Builder use cases.
Collective Core Audience Model: Multiple Individual data extensions and one or more Unified Individual data extensions are connected to the Engagement Contact Model.
